Mosaic at servicenow
Mosaic Overview
Mosaic is ServiceNow's AI Gateway and Inference Cloud platform that provides LLM capabilities to the agent orchestrator. It acts as a centralized service for executing AI/LLM requests with capability-based routing.

What is Mosaic?
Mosaic is an enterprise AI platform that:

Hosts LLM capabilities (GPT-4, Azure OpenAI, Gemini, etc.)
Routes requests based on capability IDs
Provides mTLS security for authenticated API calls
Supports streaming and non-streaming responses
Manages model deployments and configurations centrally
Think of it as ServiceNow's internal LLM gateway that abstracts away direct provider integrations.

How Mosaic is Used in Agent Orchestrator
1. LLM Provider Integration
Mosaic is configured as a custom LiteLLM provider in litellm_gaic_provider.py:

python
# Model format: gaic/<deployment_name>
# Example: "gaic/gpt-4o"
2. Capability-Based Routing
Each pipeline stage maps to a specific Mosaic capability ID:

Stage	Capability Key	Purpose
COMPACT_PLANNER	compact_planner	Simple vs Complex query classification
PLANNER1	planner1	Intent classification & agent matching
PLANNER2	planner2	Question answering & synthesis
OPENAI_AGENT_EXECUTION	openai_agent_execution	Agent-based tool execution
OPENAI_TOOL_EXECUTION	openai_tool_execution	Single tool execution
WEB_SEARCH	web_search	Web search queries
OUTPUT_REFINER	output_refiner	Response refinement
Configuration: Capability IDs are defined in litellm.yaml under providers.gaic.capability_ids.

